Hello, 

We have recently changed the project key pattern in order to allow project keys to contain also numbers at the end of the key: 

Default pattern: 
{noformat}([A-Z][A-Z]+){noformat}
New pattern: 
{noformat}([A-Z][A-Z]+([0-9]+)?{noformat}

After performing this change, we have detected that some fields (Comments, for example) were rendering incorrectly the information and a string 'null' was added. 

For example, this information 
{noformat}FA 2014 (WS-T2-LI-01; WS-T2-R-05) {noformat}
was being rendered with a 'null' in it
{noformat}FA 2014 (WS-T2-LInull-01; WS-T2-R-05){noformat}

We have checked that this information has not been altered in the database. In fact, if we edited any of the fields showing this problem, the edition box was showing the correct values.

After switching back to the original Project key pattern, this problem disappeared. 

We would like to know if this behaviour would be reproduced in the newest Jira versions. 

Thanks in advance for your help. 
Marc

